From Cloud Beginner to Award-Winning Game Developer: A Journey with AWS Cloud Institute Author: Carlie Marvel
Published: April 1, 2025
Categories: Amazon Bedrock, Amazon CloudFront, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon Q Developer, Amazon Route 53, Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3), AWS Lambda, AWS Training and Certification
Introduction When JC Boissy&rsquo;s serverless card game CloudJack-21 was honored at the 2024 AWS Game Builder Challenge, it marked a remarkable milestone in his cloud computing journey. Among 331 submissions from developers worldwide, his educational card game stood out.
This achievement is even more notable because JC had very little real-world cloud experience before joining AWS Cloud Institute ‚Äì an online training program that helps learners start cloud development in just nine months.
Career at a Crossroads JC Boissy&rsquo;s path to cloud development was far from straightforward. With years of experience transitioning from:
Software development ‚Üí Management ‚Üí IT project management JC had built a solid career in technology. But when his company closed at the end of 2023, JC found himself at a critical juncture.
Finding a New Path &ldquo;After several months of job searching, I realized something important,&rdquo; JC explains. &ldquo;Today, applying for high-level tech positions relies not just on past experience but on who you know, and more importantly, on having real technical skills.&rdquo;
The landscape had changed significantly from his early programming days. Although he had managed cloud projects as a project manager, JC had never worked directly with those technologies.
&ldquo;I remember doing pure technical work,&rdquo; he recalls. &ldquo;But I knew I needed to upskill to keep up with current technology.&rdquo;
Finding His Path with AWS Cloud Institute Initially, JC discovered AWS Cloud Institute by chance while looking for opportunities for his son. Upon reviewing the program details, he realized he was the one who needed it.
&ldquo;It had been a long time since I last studied, and technology had changed so much. I needed to get back to modern technology.&rdquo;
Full-Time Learning Commitment &ldquo;AWS Cloud Institute was truly a gift from heaven,&rdquo; JC says. &ldquo;The program provided exactly what I needed ‚Äì a structured roadmap to become a cloud developer who can build applications end-to-end. I decided to go all in, dedicating full-time effort to rebuilding my technical foundation.&rdquo;
Joining AWS Cloud Institute marked a significant commitment. Although he had managed cloud projects, JC admits:
&ldquo;Until joining AWS Cloud Institute, I had no real hands-on cloud experience ‚Äì just abstract concepts about cloud computing.&rdquo;
Comprehensive Approach What particularly attracted him to the program was its comprehensive approach.
&ldquo;The program is led by people at the source ‚Äì real AWS experts. I couldn&rsquo;t have gotten this perspective from self-studying. They helped me focus on the big picture while building practical skills.&rdquo;
JC dove into the program&rsquo;s rigorous learning curriculum, which includes:
Twelve courses in professional and technical skill development Over 150 hands-on labs Preparation for two AWS certifications He started applying new knowledge immediately, beginning with small applications.
&ldquo;I decided to start deploying small applications to build confidence,&rdquo; JC shares. &ldquo;My first project was a static website, but I knew I wanted to do more. The program gave me the foundation to tackle increasingly complex projects.&rdquo;
CloudJack-21: Where Games Meet Cloud Learning From Idea to Reality &ldquo;Initially, I wasn&rsquo;t sure whether to join the AWS Game Builder Challenge,&rdquo; JC recalls. &ldquo;But I had a Python code for a blackjack game, and during an Advanced course at AWS Cloud Institute, I had an idea ‚Äì I could turn each card into an AWS service, creating an engaging way to teach cloud concepts.&rdquo;
Game Mechanics The game CloudJack-21 combines classic blackjack mechanics with cloud computing education. Players build virtual cloud infrastructure using AWS service cards, with each card representing real services with authentic characteristics.
The game has two phases:
1. Infrastructure Building:
Players aim to build a cloud architecture with a total value under 21 2. Cloud Battle:
Players take on the role of &ldquo;Cloud Robber&rdquo; or &ldquo;Cybersecurity&rdquo; Use challenge cards or defense cards &ldquo;I wanted to create something both fun and educational,&rdquo; JC says. &ldquo;The challenge was balancing gameplay with accurate AWS service simulation.&rdquo;
Leveraging AI for Serverless Success Technologies Used To create CloudJack-21, JC leveraged AWS services:
AWS Lambda Amazon DynamoDB Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) Amazon CloudFront Amazon Route 53 AI Tools in Development As part of the AWS Game Builder Challenge requirements, JC also used AI tools like:
Amazon Q Developer PartyRock &ldquo;These tools acted like a virtual team member,&rdquo; JC explains. &ldquo;They help with everything from code suggestions to content creation, which was crucial given the tight development timeline.&rdquo;
Development Challenges But the development process wasn&rsquo;t without challenges.
&ldquo;Time constraints were a critical factor,&rdquo; JC admits. &ldquo;I worked with a very tight deadline, which pushed me to prioritize efficiency and maximize AI tools during the challenge.&rdquo;
JC also emphasizes the learning process:
&ldquo;I learned new programming languages and AWS services while building the game. This process was stressful but incredibly rewarding.&rdquo;
Recognition Among Hundreds of Entries &ldquo;Being recognized among hundreds of entries was amazing,&rdquo; JC says. &ldquo;When I saw the other winning games, I was even more proud ‚Äì these developers created truly innovative projects, and being mentioned alongside them validated my journey.&rdquo;
What Makes AWS Cloud Institute Different JC credits his rapid transformation from a cloud newcomer to an award-winning game developer to the comprehensive training program of AWS Cloud Institute.
&ldquo;Before AWS Cloud Institute, I managed cloud projects but lacked real hands-on experience. The program changed everything.&rdquo;
Program Structure The structured teaching program provides:
‚úÖ Expert AWS-led instruction
‚úÖ Over 150 hands-on labs for real experience
‚úÖ Comprehensive coverage of AWS services
‚úÖ Real-world project opportunities
‚úÖ A supportive learning community
&ldquo;The program guided me through everything I needed to build CloudJack-21 ‚Äì from basic cloud concepts to advanced serverless architecture. I couldn&rsquo;t have self-taught this.&rdquo;
Focus on Practical Application JC particularly valued the program&rsquo;s focus on practical application.
&ldquo;Every concept we learned was immediately applied through labs and projects. This hands-on approach was critical in building my confidence and skills.&rdquo;
The Power of Community One aspect of AWS Cloud Institute that JC found particularly valuable was the sense of community.
&ldquo;Having a 24/7 active Slack channel and regular office hours with AWS instructors made a huge difference,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;Whenever I faced challenges, there was always someone ready to help or provide fresh perspective.&rdquo;
Fun Fridays JC was also impressed with the Fun Fridays program.
&ldquo;These sessions focused on new topics and career advice, keeping us engaged and thinking creatively about applying our skills.&rdquo;
Looking to the Future After his success at AWS Game Builder Challenge, JC is currently:
Pursuing additional AWS certifications Seeking positions in cloud development and architecture Certifications Achieved He has earned:
‚úÖ AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner ‚úÖ AWS Certified AI Practitioner ‚úÖ AWS Certified Solutions Architect ‚Äì Associate üéØ AWS Certified Developer (upcoming) Long-term Goals &ldquo;My goal is to find a job in AWS cloud development or architecture,&rdquo; JC shares. &ldquo;I want to be part of a team building innovative cloud applications that create real impact.&rdquo;
Advice for Aspiring Cloud Developers For those inspired by his story, JC emphasizes the importance of structured learning:
&ldquo;AWS Cloud Institute provides the foundation you need to build real cloud applications. They don&rsquo;t just teach you technology but also show you how to use it creatively and effectively.&rdquo;
Start Small and Practice JC also emphasizes the importance of hands-on practice:
&ldquo;Theory is important, but nothing beats actually building things. Start small, experiment, and don&rsquo;t be afraid to make mistakes ‚Äì that&rsquo;s how you learn and grow.&rdquo;
Final Message &ldquo;This journey showed me that with proper training and determination, you can go from understanding cloud concepts to building award-winning applications in less than a year,&rdquo; JC shares. &ldquo;CloudJack-21 is just the beginning.&rdquo;
Start Your Own Success Story Want to build your own cloud computing success story?
Learn more about AWS Cloud Institute at: awscloudinstitute.com
Conclusion JC Boissy&rsquo;s story is living proof of what&rsquo;s possible when you have the right resources, guidance, and willingness to learn. From managing cloud projects without hands-on experience to building an award-winning application, AWS Cloud Institute opened new doors for his career.
If you&rsquo;re considering entering cloud computing, remember: It&rsquo;s never too late to start, and with proper commitment and appropriate support, you can build a solid career in the cloud.
